This paper deals with probabilistic reasoning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). It also touches on the concept of conditional independence, which is relevant to cryptography and security (cs.CR) as well as information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper proposes a formalization using Pointwise Circumscription, which is a logical reasoning technique that falls under the sub-category of symbolic AI (cs.SI).
